page.title: 12RAILWAY 2
page.content: When the trains went past they made seeds fly to each side of the track and all the trees grew there.Now the railway track has grown over with grass and trees.The thing that stops it from being a nice place is the rubbish.People just throw old carpets and things out instead of taking it to the local tip.They could phone Durham County Council to take it away.The railway used to run from Darlington to Barnard Castle.The railway used to go underneath the A1M motorway but there is a tip there now because the farmer wanted his two fields attached together the name of the farmer is Mr.Mac Andrews he lives in Hall Farm Archdeacon Newton.
